      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> the only spirit-skulled Deadwatcher chieftain to last a full week inside the castle — risen the next night as a <strong>fext</strong>, now mistress of the guest wing (B29), served by the orc-spirit wraiths of B33. Found staring out her arrow slit, lost in thought; <strong>she won't attack until spoken to or attacked</strong>, then fights in eerie silence. Big noise in B28 brings her in 1d4 rounds. <strong>The kill:</strong> the dead orc in B7 carries a <em>+1 striking obsidian battleaxe</em> — the castle's one ready tool for ending her (the blood-scrawled warnings in B7/B13/B25 are her victims' work). <strong>Permanently slain, her grateful spirit sighs thanks and infuses her own axe</strong> — it becomes the sinister intelligent weapon @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-items.Item.ch5UkwarAxe00001]{Ukwar}.</p>",
      "publication": {
